column5: Well, figured out some good patterns at a derby in Big Island Lake of the Woods last weekend, so me and some family members decided to head out again with lesser crowds.  Head out tomorrow am, and were gonna try to hit walleye/crappie on a few good reefs we found. The deadstick/lipless crank combo was on fire the day after the derby (D'oh).  Trying out a new to me Vexilar flasher tomorrow too, can't wait!!!  Who else is heading out? and what are y'all fishing for?
